where locals open channels with foreigners, and where skeptics of contact debate naifs. Tacking across geopolitical borders, the book demonstrates how contact and channel shift in significance over time, through events and political relations, in social conflict, and in conversation. The author suggests that Cold War preoccupations and strategies have marked theoretical models of communication and mediation, even while infusing everyday, practical technologies for intuition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aCold WarxInfluence. 0aParanoiaxPolitical aspects. 0aTelepathy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican history.  aanthropology.  acold war history.  acold war propaganda.  acold war.  acommunication failure.  acommunication.  aempathy drills.  aempathy.  aethnography.  ageopolitical borders.  aglobal history.  ainternational.  aintuition.  alinguistics.  amedia.  amediation.  aperformance.  apolitical relations.  apolitics.  apropaganda.  arelationship with russia.  arussia.  arussian history.  asocial conflict.  asocial science.  atechnology.  atelepathy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029428840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967458/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY